@startuml facet-upgrade-workflow
title "Diamond Facet Upgrade Workflow (ERC2535)"

actor Admin as "Contract Admin"
participant Diamond as "Diamond Proxy"
participant DiamondCut as "DiamondCutFacet"
participant NewFacet as "New Facet Implementation"
participant OldFacet as "Old Facet Implementation"

== Facet Upgrade Process ==

Admin -> Diamond: diamondCut(facetCuts, init, initCalldata)
activate Diamond

Diamond -> DiamondCut: delegatecall diamondCut()
activate DiamondCut

alt Add New Facet
    DiamondCut -> DiamondCut: addFunctions(newFacetAddress, selectors)
    note right: Maps function selectors\nto new facet address
    
else Replace Existing Facet
    DiamondCut -> DiamondCut: replaceFunctions(newFacetAddress, selectors)
    note right: Updates selector mapping\nfrom old to new facet
    
else Remove Facet
    DiamondCut -> DiamondCut: removeFunctions(facetAddress, selectors)
    note right: Removes function selectors\nfrom diamond storage
end

DiamondCut -> DiamondCut: emit DiamondCut(facetCuts, init, initCalldata)

alt Initialization Required
    DiamondCut -> Diamond: init.delegatecall(initCalldata)
    note right: Executes initialization\nlogic if provided
end

DiamondCut --> Diamond: success
deactivate DiamondCut

Diamond --> Admin: transaction success
deactivate Diamond

== Function Call Routing (Post-Upgrade) ==

actor User
User -> Diamond: someFunction()
activate Diamond

Diamond -> Diamond: _fallback()
Diamond -> Diamond: lookup facet for msg.sig
Diamond -> NewFacet: delegatecall someFunction()
activate NewFacet

NewFacet -> NewFacet: execute business logic
NewFacet --> Diamond: return result
deactivate NewFacet

Diamond --> User: return result
deactivate Diamond

note over Diamond, NewFacet: All function calls now route\nto the upgraded facet implementation

== Storage Considerations ==

note over DiamondCut
    **Storage Safety:**
    - Facet upgrades preserve storage layout
    - New facets can add storage variables
    - Existing storage slots remain intact
    - Diamond storage pattern prevents collisions
end note

note over Diamond
    **Upgrade Benefits:**
    - Gas efficient (only update changed facets)
    - Unlimited contract size
    - Modular functionality updates
    - Preserves state and addresses
end note

@enduml
